# "Orders" Means the Orders List Page

When the user talks about **orders** (e.g. "fix the orders page", "add a column to orders", "orders table"), assume they mean:

- **Orders.tsx** (the orders list/overview page)

**Not** OrderDetail.tsx (the single-order detail page) unless they explicitly say "order detail", "order detail page", or "OrderDetail".

## Examples

- "Sort orders by date" → work in **Orders.tsx**
- "Add a filter to orders" → work in **Orders.tsx**
- "Fix the orders table" → work in **Orders.tsx**
- "Change the order detail header" → work in **OrderDetail.tsx** (explicit)
